<br>
*Absolutely no begging: once is asking, twice is reminding, thrice is begging.<br>
<br>
*Treat fellow members with respect, be considerate.<br>
<br>
*Keep guild chat clean and free of vulgarity.<br>
<br>
*New members must be recommended by two current members &amp; have grouping time with a minimum of two members. (Alternate rules apply for RL Refferals...still subject to officer approval.)<br>
<br>
*Officer/Council who invites the new member will be required to explain rules and guidelines...(and also will be ultimately responsible for disbanding said person should it be needed)  ALL NEW MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO POST BASIC CHARACTER INFORMATION IN THE MEMBERS AREA....this helps us keep track of what we have and how everyone is doing.<br>
<br>
*Do not dishonor/discredit the guild with poor actions/attitude...this will result in immediate disbanding.<br>
<br>
*Officers will be nominated by current officers, Council, and Leader. Officers must be level 45 or above.<br>
<br>
*All disciplinary actions and warnings will be discussed in officer chat channel to address the issue and choose a course of action.<br>
<br>
*Membership may be revoked by; Leader, Council, or two officers.<br>
<br>
*Raid Rules will be determined by the Raid leader and are not open for debate.  Loot will be distributed fairly, with NEED before GREED as the most important policy.  Any dispute over loot will be settled by Officers (this decision process should result in a unanymous decision that all officers agree is fair and appropriate)<br>
<br>
*Any disputes of the rules, the Leader and council will settle, with a final and binding decision.<br>
